name: cities
description: JumpStart International's January 2011 Georgia files have been exported from a central database built on the open source OpenStreetMap stack.  All field work for this project was conducted during 2010 by JumpStart's 10 regional Georgia offices.  The geographic coverage area for the complete data set is the entirety of the country of Georgia, excluding the two separatist regions of South Ossetia and Abkhazia.  The files contain spatial information for a series of feature types.  These features include country boundaries, road and rail network, landuse, hydrography, settlement points, and points of interest.
